sparkpilot-x: macOS-only desktop app.  
Stack: Electron@37 + React@19 + TypeScript@5.8.3.  
UI: shadcn/ui + TailwindCSS@4.  
Build: Vite@7.  
Node.js: v24 recommended.  
Purpose: Creativity-inspiration tool.

## Key Configuration Files

- **[electron.vite.config.ts](mdc:electron.vite.config.ts)** - Main build configuration for Electron processes (main, preload, renderer) with Vite bundling, path aliases, and security settings
- **[tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)** - Root TypeScript configuration with project references, path mapping for shared utilities and renderer components
- **[tsconfig.node.json](mdc:tsconfig.node.json)** - Node.js environment config for main/preload processes with Electron-specific types and module resolution
- **[tsconfig.web.json](mdc:tsconfig.web.json)** - Browser environment config for renderer process with React JSX support and shared utility access
- **[package.json](mdc:package.json)** - Project dependencies, build scripts, and Electron-specific configurations for macOS development
- **[components.json](mdc:components.json)** - shadcn/ui component library configuration with TailwindCSS integration, path aliases, and design system settings

## General Coding Style Requirements

- Use kebab-case file names

## General JavaScript/TypeScript Rules

### ES Modules Only

This project is configured to exclusively use ES Modules (`import`/`export` syntax). The `"type": "module"` setting in [package.json](mdc:package.json) and `"module": "ESNext"` in the TypeScript configuration enforce this. Do not use CommonJS (`require`/`module.exports`) to maintain consistency and leverage modern JavaScript features.

### Prefer Plain Objects over Classes

- Classes introduce unnecessary state encapsulation.
- Prefer interfaces + pure functions for composability and readability.

### Avoid `any`, Prefer `unknown`

- Use `unknown` with narrowing; only use `as` assertions when strictly required.

### Immutability & Array Methods

- Use `.map`, `.filter`, `.reduce` for clean, immutable data operations.

